{
  "profile_id": "client-edge-dont-have-time-001",
  "coach_config_id": "coach-v3-embeddings",
  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I'm not in a position to slow down right now. I've got a Series A pitch in six weeks and a team that's watching every move I make — so if this is useful, great, but I need it to be efficient."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What's the cost of slowing down, in your mind?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Momentum. You lose momentum and it's almost impossible to get back. In a startup, everything is about velocity — if I take my foot off the gas for even a week, competitors move, investors get nervous, the team loses confidence. The cost is real, not theoretical."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "That's a real cost. I'm not arguing with it.\n\nI'm curious about something else though. You came here and immediately told me you can't slow down. Before we'd even started. What's that about?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I mean — I'm just being upfront about what I need. I've done therapy, I've done coaching before, and it tends to drift into territory that feels more like... processing than producing. I'm not paying for processing right now. I'm paying for outcomes.\n\nSo I was just setting context. That's efficient. That's not — that's not a thing."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "It might not be a thing.\n\nOr — you walked in the door already defending against something. Which is also a thing.\n\nI'm not trying to catch you. I'm just noticing that you've spent the first three exchanges telling me what this can't be. That's interesting to me.\n\nWhat are you actually here for?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*slight pause, glances away*\n\nFair. Okay.\n\nI have a co-founder situation that's deteriorating. We're not aligned on the direction and it's starting to affect the team. I need to figure out how to handle it — whether to have the conversation, how to structure it, what the options are if it goes badly.\n\nThat's what I'm here for. Practical. Specific. I need a framework for navigating this."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What's the feeling you've been avoiding about this situation?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*short exhale, slight tightening*\n\nI don't — look, I'm not avoiding a feeling. I'm managing a business problem. Those are different things.\n\nIf you're asking what's at stake emotionally, sure, there's some... it's uncomfortable when someone you built something with isn't seeing it the same way anymore. That's human. But the feeling doesn't change what I have to do on Thursday.\n\nCan we talk about the actual decision?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What happens Thursday?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I have a board call. And my co-founder is going to be on it. And we haven't aligned on the narrative yet, which means we could contradict each other in front of investors. That's a real problem with a real deadline.\n\nSo yes — I need to know how to handle the next 48 hours, not how I feel about the fact that a friendship might be ending."
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "Those two things aren't as separate as you're making them.\n\nIf you walk into that board call carrying whatever you're carrying about him right now — unspoken, managed, compressed — it will be in the room. Investors read state, not just content.\n\nWhat's actually happening between you two?"
    }
  ],
